        <p data-uuid="517de76e9eef475ebca50b66d8acc69f">Before his trial, Turner made a confession. He expressed his belief that the revolt was justified and worth his death: “I am willing to suffer the fate that awaits me.” Turner was executed on November 11, 1831. After the rebellion, many states strengthened their slave codes. The new codes placed stricter control on enslaved people. Despite resistance, slavery continued to spread.</p>
